<TITLE> BFF award night set for Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 28 (bdnews24.com)The Bangladesh Football Federation awards will be held on Wednesday the 29th of July at the National Sports Council Tower auditorium. State minister for youth and sports, Ahad Ali Sarker, will present B League champions Dhaka Abahani and runners-up Mohammedan Sporting Club with their trophies at the event. The two teams will also receive cheques for Tk 10 lakh and Tk 5 respectively. Third-placed Sheikh Russell and fourth-placed Brothers Union will receive Tk 3 lakh and Tk 2 lakh each. Awards for the best player and highest scorer in the league will also be presented. The award ceremony will also see silverware presented to the champions and runners-up of the First, Second and Third Division Leagues. A musical show will follow the presentation ceremony. The award night was originally scheduled for Saturday the 26th July, but was changed due to 'unavoidable circumstances 
